<paragraph blockId="10.[470,869,1271,1328]" box="[579,763,1304,1328]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">
(
<figureCitation box="[587,754,1304,1328]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figures 12–14</figureCitation>
)
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,243,1385,1409]" box="[138,243,1385,1409]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">
<emphasis box="[138,243,1385,1409]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,1434,1522]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">
Aedeagal median rod dorsally with strong subbasal process (
<figureCitation box="[835,951,1434,1458]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 12</figureCitation>
); aedeagal apodeme broadened, horizontally flattened (
<figureCitation box="[572,688,1466,1490]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figure 14</figureCitation>
); ventral branch of aedeagal apodeme sclerotized, slightly expanded apically, with a projection submedially (
<figureCitation box="[955,1127,1498,1522]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Figures 12, 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,259,1579,1603]" box="[138,259,1579,1603]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">
<emphasis box="[138,259,1579,1603]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">Description</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="10.[138,1185,1628,1684]" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">
Some characters commonly seen in 
<taxonomicName box="[582,740,1628,1652]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Apsiphortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="longiciliata">
<emphasis box="[582,601,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">A</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[622,740,1628,1652]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="2715">longiciliata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are not referred to in the following description.
</paragraph>
<caption ID-DOI="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" ID-Zenodo-Dep="4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716" startId="11.[125,194,790,809]" targetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" targetPageId="11">
<paragraph blockId="11.[125,1173,790,889]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">
Figures 12–14. 
<taxonomicName authority="Chen" authorityName="Chen" authorityYear="2007" box="[277,484,790,809]" class="Insecta" family="Drosophilidae" genus="Apsiphortica" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="xui" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[277,422,790,809]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Apsiphortica xui</emphasis>
Chen
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[497,576,790,809]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<emphasis bold="true" box="[588,602,790,809]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">„</emphasis>
. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph blockId="11.[125,1172,928,984]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">
<emphasis box="[125,214,928,952]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Thorax.</emphasis>
Yellow, with five narrow black stripes on scutum and a few dark brown patches on pleura. Scutellum grey-brown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[125,1098,1023,1047]" box="[125,1098,1023,1047]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">
<emphasis box="[125,236,1023,1047]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Abdomen.</emphasis>
Tergites yellow, each with broad, dark brown band on posterior margin.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="11.[125,1172,1087,1271]" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">
<emphasis box="[125,313,1087,1111]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Male terminalia.</emphasis>
Epandrium strongly protruded at anteroventral corners, with about 28 setae near posterior margin and pubescence except for anteroventral margin (
<figureCitation box="[1042,1158,1119,1143]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figure 12</figureCitation>
). Tenth sternite with non-pubescent median piece (
<figureCitation box="[703,819,1151,1175]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figure 13</figureCitation>
). Hypandrium arched, slightly broadened anteromedially (
<figureCitation box="[447,562,1183,1207]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figure 14</figureCitation>
). Parameres separated from each other (
<figureCitation captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figures 12, 14</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal outer membrane with about eight sclerotized small pieces (
<figureCitation box="[986,1158,1215,1239]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figures 12, 14</figureCitation>
). Aedeagal median rod apically round, basally fused with aedeagal apodeme (
<figureCitation box="[988,1158,1247,1271]" captionStart="Figures 12–14" captionStartId="11.[125,194,790,809]" captionTargetBox="[174,1125,140,752]" captionTargetId="figure-228@11.[170,1128,133,754]" captionTargetPageId="11" captionText="Figures 12–14. Apsiphortica xui Chen, sp. nov., „. (12) Epandrium, cercus, surstylus, hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, lateral view. (13) Surstylus and 10th sternite, ventral view. (14) Epandrium (part), hypandrium, gonopod, paramere, aedeagal median rod, and aedeagal apodeme, ventral view. For abbreviations see Figures 1–3. Scale bars: 0.1 mm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.4658316" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/4658316/files/figure.png" pageId="11" pageNumber="2716">Figures 12, 14</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
